<br>
What I do is buff myself completely, then self haste, tag a mob, pull him to a &quot;safe&quot; area and then beat on him until hes dead.  Then I click off &quot;Valor&quot; and heal myself using the DW Helm.  Then when I have half a health bubble to heal left I re-Valor myself and am pretty much good to go.  I can make 2 blue bubbles an hour doing this (provided I am lucky and get consistant blues).<br>
<br>
In Solb it is best to run to the Sola zone (or come through Sola to the Solb zone) and fight the stuff there (I am talking the lower solb/sola zone).  You get very good xp down there and if things get too hot you can zone and heal.  I plan on going back there once I hit 54 because my Root doesn't hold the mobs as long as Ensnare will.<br>
<br>
You can also solo spiders in Velks (I know you say you hate them) with DW helm/bracer combo.  Stun with bracer, heal with helm and beat on with weapon. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You can do one at a time this way (though it can get hairy without a good root spell if more than one comes).<br>
<br>
I have also heard you can solo at Seb zone-in but I have never tried it (and would not without a gate potion).<br>
<br>
Depending on your level you can also fight the Freeport Militia.  It is the best way to Roleplay your Paladin and can be good xp (and loads of fun when lower level Paladins cheer you on). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Crowsfool Fortunes<br>
Paladin of the 53rd Holy Season<br>
